<p>This plugin adds "List Mode" toggles to the Add/Edit Container pages, allowing you to edit environment variables, ports, and volumes as text lists instead of individual form fields.</p>

<p><strong>How to use:</strong></p>
<ol>
  <li>Go to Docker &gt; Add Container or edit an existing container</li>
  <li>Enable "Advanced View" in the upper right corner</li>
  <li>Look for "List Mode" buttons next to Environment Variables, Ports, and Paths sections</li>
  <li>Click to toggle between form and list editing modes</li>
</ol>

<p><strong>Supported formats:</strong></p>
<ul>
  <li>Environment: <code>NAME=VALUE</code></li>
  <li>Ports: <code>HOST:CONTAINER/PROTOCOL</code></li>
  <li>Paths: <code>/host/path:/container/path:MODE</code></li>
</ul>
